More than 3.5 million people in Somalia's Galgaduud are facing the threat of food and water shortages due to continuously worsening drought. Â The number of people facing the crisis may rise to 4.6 million, nearly one-third of the country's population, by May next year. Somalia, a war-torn country, becomes increasingly vulnerable to crises as it has experienced more than 30 climate-related hazards since 1990, including 12 droughts and 19 floods. (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)